consensus text: strata of [underline]shist and of sandstone[/underline] of the
common kind and having nothing peculiar
The same Basaltic strata which occur
in [underline]Teesdale[/underline] and which are represented in
this sketch extend into the north into alstone
more: and they have been traced more than
thirty miles and they are uniform[deletion]a[/deletion]ly found
between the same shistous strata; and the
shist below them and incumbent upon them
soft though when acted upon by a Heat
much below that necessary for fusing
